<date id="FFBD1006FFF2FF9BFBECFDA2FB105540" box="[1117,1245,523,549]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" value="2021-07-03">3 July 2021</date>
; M. P. Roa. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF2FF9BFF70FD87FEBD552D" box="[193,368,558,584]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Thrixopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF2FF9BFF70FD87FE81552D" box="[193,332,558,584]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Thrixopelma</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF2FF9BFECCFD87FDE5552C" box="[381,552,558,585]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The wasp dragged the paralyzed tarantula backwards on the ground, dorsal side upward, grasping the base of its left foreleg with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF2FF9BFB00FDF9FAED550F" author="Roa MP" box="[1201,1312,592,618]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" refId="ref26337" refString="Roa MP. 2021. Cazandoimagenes. Available at https: // www. instagram. com / p / CQ 3 p 9 v 5 sXBn /. (Last accessed 5 December 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Roa 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
